  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To strengthen National Toxics Network&apos;s (NTN) efforts to facilitate regional and international efforts to grow the environmental health movement, work for a toxics-free future in the Australasian and Pacific region, and further their campaigns against hazardous waste, pesticides, toxic chemicals, and mercury. NTN will produce a number of technical reports and present findings to other NGOs and organizations involved in work to eliminate hazardous waste (especially in relation to electronic and persistent organic pollutants); work with the World Wildlife Fund to promote biological agriculture; participate in national negotiations related to mercury; produce a technical report on Coal Seam Gas; and co-author the UNEP Climate Change and Chemicals Report</narrative>
